SELECT COUNT(*) FROM orders; 
SELECT MIN(order_date), MAX(order_date) FROM orders; 
SELECT SUM(revenue) FROM orders;
Break down:
SELECT COUNT(*): Count ALL the rows of the table and print the total 
<br>
FROM: indicates which table to pull the information from. **NOTE unless stated otherwise this will be the general idea of what FROM is doing going foward, keep this in mind.
<br>
SELECT MIN, MAX: Here we are asking for the minimum and maximum values of the specified table. (the example points to order dates in this case.)
